ANS: All of the above

4.3> Choose the correct statement. Restriction on static methods are: I. They can only call other static methods. II. They must only access static data. III. They cannot refer this or super in any way.
ANS; I, II, and III

4.4> What would be the behavior if this() and super() were used in a method?
ANS: compile-time error

4.5> The static member functions ____________________
ANS: Can be called using class name

